Text: Many of Tunisia's sacred cows have fallen, from technocrat Prime Minister Youssef Chahed to Defense Minister Abdelkarim Zbidi and moderate Islamist Ennahda's Abdelfattah Mourou, all of whom are perceived as having presided over the country's gradual decline and fall.   I want the government to provide jobs and money to young people for projects, said Khalil Mlouki, a univeristy graduate who was among the 54% of Tunisians to withhold their vote.
